</div>
<button class="accordion">What does the Equality Act mean?</button>
<div class="panel">
<p>The Equality Act is a law which protects you from discrimination. It means that discrimination or unfair treatment based on specific personal characteristics, such as age, is now against the law in almost all cases.</p>
</div>
<button class="accordion">What is equality, diversity and human rights in health and social care?</button>
<div class="panel">
<p>Equality, diversity and human rights in health and social care is the act of promoting equality and respecting diversity to ensure that people are valued and have the same access to all opportunities whatever their differences. The act also protects individuals who experience discrimination by association with someone who has a protected characteristic.</p>
